WATER and Sanitation Minister Senzo Mchunu says the Giyani Water Project has been an embarrassment to his department. This is because the project in Giyani, Limpopo, has already spent R3,2 billion, which has not been accounted for. It now needs a further R1 billion to ensure installation of pipes and the upgrade of the Nandoni Water Treatment Works. ALSO READ | Students: We are terrorised by cops The project was launched in 2014 by former president Jacob Zuma and it collapsed in 2018 after corruption allegations. Mchunu was on a week-long visit to Limpopo to access the progress made. ALSO READ | Life’s tough for 'nyaopes My Friend’ Mchunu said he was satisfied the process of bringing water to Giyani was on course. The project is expected to be completed in September and will benefit around 55 villages and more than 240 000 people. Mchunu said a pipeline to bring water from treatment works to Malamulele and surrounding areas was also installed.